title: Compilation suddenly stopped working; Cargo clean fixed the problem

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
Compilation suddenly stopped working. Rustc only reported the error below on every compilation attempt. I messed around with a rather complex trait involving many (16 at the moment) associated types. After running `cargo clean` and rebuilding the project from scratch, the application compiled again and ran as good as always. ### Code ```Rust // As the code is not open-sourced, I cannot share an example.
